# Roles

## Personal User

The first version of Revia is designed primarily for personal use.

A user can:

* Create decks
* Create lessons
* Create cards
* Review cards
* Track learning progress
* Import learning content
* Export learning content

No sharing or collaboration is included in Version 1.

---

## Admin

Initially, the admin is simply the application owner.

The admin has all user capabilities, along with the ability to:

* Manage application settings
* Import sample content
* Maintain default decks
* Manage future platform features

The system should be designed so additional roles can be added later without changing the core architecture.

Possible future roles:

* Creator
* Moderator
* Public Deck Publisher

These are intentionally outside the scope of Version 1.

---

# Content Import

Version 1 supports importing learning content through a JSON file.

The import system should be generic so that the same format works for any subject.

Future versions may also support:

* CSV
* Excel
* Markdown
* PDF (AI-assisted)
* Custom `.revia` package format

JSON is the only required import format for the first release.

---

# JSON Structure

```json
{
  "deck": {
    "title": "Kannada Basics",
    "description": "Beginner vocabulary and phrases",
    "tags": ["language", "beginner"]
  },
  "lessons": [
    {
      "title": "Greetings",
      "description": "Basic greetings",
      "cards": [
        {
          "front": "Hello",
          "back": "ನಮಸ್ಕಾರ",
          "pronunciation": "Namaskara",
          "example": "ನಮಸ್ಕಾರ, ಹೇಗಿದ್ದೀರ?",
          "notes": "Formal greeting",
          "tags": ["greeting", "beginner"]
        },
        {
          "front": "Thank you",
          "back": "ಧನ್ಯವಾದ",
          "pronunciation": "Dhanyavada",
          "example": "ತುಂಬ ಧನ್ಯವಾದ",
          "notes": "",
          "tags": ["polite"]
        }
      ]
    }
  ]
}
```

Only the following fields are required:

* Deck title
* Lesson title
* Card front
* Card back

All other fields are optional.

